1Time, African Rainbow, Santam May Move in Early Trading in Johannesburg

-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 
2011-08-30T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-30/1time-african-rainbow-santam-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close. The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index climbed
for a third day, adding 72.37, or 0.2 percent, to 30,365.13 by
the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  1Time Holdings Ltd. (1TM)  (1TM SJ): The low-cost airline and
technical maintenance company posted a loss per share of as much
as 13.9 cents for the six months to June 30. The stock ended
unchanged at 40 cents.  African Rainbow Minerals Ltd. (ARI)  : The producer of
coal, platinum and nickel releases earnings for the year to June
30. Earnings per share are expected to be as much as 89 percent
higher than the year earlier, the group said in a trading
statement on Aug. 19. The shares rose 2 percent to 180.35 rand.  Anglo American Platinum Ltd. (AMS SJ): South Africa’s
National Union of Mineworkers said it’s “likely” to sign a
wage agreement with the world’s largest platinum producer, Oupa
Komane, the union’s chief negotiator at the company, said by
mobile phone yesterday. The stock increased 0.1 percent to
570.84 rand.  Kaydav Group Ltd. (KDV)  : The wood board distributor and
wholesaler said earnings per share doubled to 3.2 cents in the
six months to June 30. The stock ended unchanged at 36 cents.  Murray & Roberts Holdings Ltd. (MUR)  : South Africa’s
second-biggest construction company reports earnings for the
year to June 30. The group posted a diluted loss per share of as
much as 6.15 rand, it said in a trading statement on Aug. 19.
The stock gained 0.3 percent to 27.65 rand.  Rainbow Chicken Ltd. (RBW)  : The country’s largest
producer of chicken said earnings per share rose 7.6 percent in
the 15 months to June 30. The shares added 1.2 percent to 17
rand.  Santam Ltd. (SNT)  : South Africa’s largest property and
casualty insurer releases earnings for the six months to June
30. The stock advanced 1.3 percent to 130.65 rand.  Sovereign Food Investments (SOV)  Ltd: The poultry
producer said Chief Executive Officer  Mike Davis  has stepped
down. Board Chairman Charles Davies will take over as CEO until
a replacement is appointed. Shares in the company ended
unchanged at 5 rand.  Village Main Reef Ltd. (VIL SJ): The mining investment
company said it has received permission from South Africa’s
Department of Mineral Resources to resume operations at its Tau
Lekoa mine after the death of a worker on Aug. 24. The stock
ended unchanged at 1.38 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Gunnion in Johannesburg at 
 sgunnion@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
